The Dellius addressed is undoubtedly Q. Dellius, whom Messala nieknamed desultor bellorum civilium because oi his frequent changes of allegiance during the civil wars. ln 31 uc. he returned finally to Octavian's side, and later became one of his trusted courtiers. The place of the ode here was determined both by the similarity of its sub- ject with that of 2, and especially by Horace's desire to give Dellius a place next Sallust. Cf. intr. n. to 2, 1.
